I lied... to her.

1580
02:04:36.160 --> 02:04:38.680
She thought she'd seen you.

1581
02:04:38.720 --> 02:04:40.600
Why lie?

1582
02:04:40.640 --> 02:04:45.400
Dickie and Peter
together. That's just too good gossip.

1583
02:04:45.440 --> 02:04:47.320
Or Tom and Peter. even.

1584
02:04:47.360 --> 02:04:49.800
That would be
even better gossip.

1585
02:04:49.880 --> 02:04:52.040
Really? Why?

1586
02:04:56.680 --> 02:05:00.960
I-l. um--
I'm completely lost.

1587
02:05:03.520 --> 02:05:05.360
I know.

1588
02:05:06.600 --> 02:05:09.600
I'm sorry. Peter.

1589
02:05:09.680 --> 02:05:11.560
I'm lost.

1590
02:05:14.560 --> 02:05:17.800
I'm gonna be stuck
in the basement. aren't I?

1591
02:05:17.880 --> 02:05:21.040
Aren't I?

1592
02:05:21.120 --> 02:05:22.960
That's my--

1593
02:05:25.920 --> 02:05:27.800
Terrible...

1594
02:05:29.080 --> 02:05:31.080
and alone...

1595
02:05:31.160 --> 02:05:34.440
and dark.

1596
02:05:34.520 --> 02:05:37.120
And I've lied...

1597
02:05:37.160 --> 02:05:40.120
about who I am...

1598
02:05:40.200 --> 02:05:42.120
and where I am.

1599
02:05:42.200 --> 02:05:44.600
Now no one'll ever find me.

1600
02:05:46.120 --> 02:05:48.360
What do you mean.
lied about who you are?

1601
02:05:48.440 --> 02:05:51.000
I always thought
it'd be better...

1602
02:05:51.040 --> 02:05:54.040
to be a fake somebody...

1603
02:05:54.080 --> 02:05:56.920
than a real nobody.

1604
02:05:56.960 --> 02:05:59.720
What are you talking about?
You're not a nobody.

1605
02:05:59.800 --> 02:06:02.200
That's the last thing
you are.

1606
02:06:09.320 --> 02:06:12.760
Peter.

1607
02:06:12.800 --> 02:06:15.280
Tell me some good things
about Tom Ripley.

1608
02:06:17.080 --> 02:06:19.600
No. don't get up.
Don't get up. Don't get up.

1609
02:06:22.440 --> 02:06:24.280
Just--

1610
02:06:26.960 --> 02:06:30.560
Just tell me some nice things...
about Tom Ripley.

1611
02:06:33.520 --> 02:06:36.480
"Good things
about Tom Ripley."

1612
